  "sessions": [
    {
      "artist": "D Rose",
      "details": "one and only. Recorded: 1988-04-08. No known commercial release. Tony Wilson the producer came to see D Rose at the Bull & Gate in Kentish Town one night. The band got the call shortly after for a slot on the Friday Rock Show. They went to Maida Vale to the BBC studios there and recorded four tracks for the show which Tommy Vance duly aired on the 22/04/88. This helped the band immensely as they had a gig shortly after at the Sir George Robey pub as support to the Pink Fairies who never showed up. Luckily for D Rose, most of the crowd which filled the place had actually come to see them anyway and a great night was had by all."
    }
  ],
